modules.description: This module defines a collection of module types used to implement custom ocamlbuild plugins, covering operations for handling ordered types with printing, set and list manipulations, string and pathname operations, command execution, glob patterns, logging, and plugin-specific interfaces. It works with abstract data types representing build tags, file paths, shell commands, and configuration options. Concrete use cases include extending ocamlbuild with custom dependency resolution, adding new command-line options, or integrating alternative build tools through the plugin system.
